title: The Bachelorette's Zac Efron-wannabe Kayde Wilkie is a stripper with stage name 'Zach Effron'
text:
He's The Bachelorette contestant who wore a Baywatch costume and claimed to look like Zac Efron on the red carpet.

And it turns out luxury car salesman Kayde Wilkie, 25, is also a stripper with the stage name 'Zach Effron'.

The handsome hunk is listed with Perth stripping agency Top Shelf Entertainment and is very open about his association with them.

'Ready to bust out Magic Mike moves': The Bachelorette's Zac Efron-wannabe Kayde Wilkie (right) is a stripper who goes by the stage name of 'Zach Effron'

Kayde's alias Zach Effron is listed as a stripper and waiter with 'SWAT team seat' and 'Magic Mike' skills on the Top Shelf Entertainment official website.

Rather tellingly, Kayde's Bachelorette profile says that he is 'always ready to bust out some 'sweet Magic Mike moves''.

The 25-year-old's stripper profile also reveals some previously-unknown hobbies, including playing the guitar, mixed martial arts and eating steak.

If you say so! On Wednesday night's episode of The Bachelorette, Kayde wore a Baywatch costume and claimed to look like Zac Efron on the red carpet

In May, the hunk posted a photo of himself suited up as he stepped off the official Top Shelf Entertainment bus and walked down a red carpet to Perth's Crown Casino.

'Was an apostle banger partying with Joseph Turner and the Rest of the boys at Top Dog Entertainment,' Kayde captioned the stylish snap.

The luxury car salesman's Bachelorette profile takes on new meaning with knowledge of his second profession.

He is described as being 'anything but shy' and wanting to help people 'who battle with insecurities and social acceptance'.

The boys are back in town! In May, Kayde posted a photo of himself suited up as he stepped off the official Top Shelf Entertainment bus and walked down a red carpet to Crown Casino

Obscure reference? The 25-year-old confused Angie Kent, 29, with his costume as he later revealed he was a car salesman

On Wednesday night's episode of The Bachelorette, the 25-year-old arrived in a lifeguard costume, which left Angie Kent, 29, confused when he revealed he was a car salesman.

'You... you're not, like, David Hasselhoff though?' Ange asked him, prompting Kayde to tell her he was dressed as Zac Efron from 2017's Baywatch movie.

'Oh my God! The fact that I didn't pick up on the Zac Efron vibe was super cringe,' remarked Angie.
